                        <summary>
                            <p>On the eastern wall section of the southern façade, lowest inscription. 10th regnal year of Kōpparakesarivarman = probably Uttamacōḻa (<foreign>circa</foreign> 981 CE). In continuation of the line 4, there is a description of another four lines of a land containing <foreign>catirattu</foreign>, <foreign>vāykkal</foreign>, <foreign>kaṇṇāṟṟu</foreign>, directions, etc. It does not seem to be connected, although it is the same writing.</p>
                            
                        </summary>
